# Laravel Backend

- Use Form Request classes for validation when logic grows; inline validation OK for simple endpoints
- Return API Resources from controllers, not raw models
- Business logic in models/scopes; keep controllers thin
- Use Enums in `app/Enums/` for status, gender, categories
- Authorize with Policies (`CatListingPolicy`, `ConversationPolicy`)
- Feature tests for API endpoints in `tests/Feature/Api/`

```php
// ✅ GOOD — scoped query + resource
return CatListingResource::collection(
    CatListing::query()->with(['owner', 'photos', 'traits'])->paginate()
);

// ❌ BAD — raw array from controller
return response()->json(CatListing::all());
```
